thread.title: Azamuddin keeps JDT on guard against Felda
thread.title_full: Azamuddin keeps JDT on guard against Felda

title: Azamuddin keeps JDT on guard against Felda
text:
PETALING JAYA: Johor Darul Ta’zim (JDT) winger Azamuddin Akil reckons that Felda United will not be affected by their off-field problems in their FA Cup second-round clash at the Tun Abdul Razak Stadium in Jengka tonight. 
Felda were left in a lurch after head coach Azmi Mohamed resigned abruptly last week after only three Super League matches. 
Azamuddin, who is known as Alex, believes that Felda still have enough quality to derail JDT’s title defence. 
“Felda were our main rivals for the Super League crown last season. I don’t think their quality has dropped drastically just because they don’t have a head coach,” said Azamuddin. 
“They have retained most of the players from last season’s squad like Shukor (Adan), Norshahrul (Idlan Talaha) and Hadin (Azman). They are top players. I’m sure they will be looking to bounce back against us. 
“We can’t be going into the match expecting our rivals to be distracted. 
“We need to get the job done and it’s our target to retain the FA Cup this season.” 
The Southern Tigers, under new coach Benjamin Mora of Mexico, have yet to get into stride so far in their Super League title defence. They are seventh with five points from a win and two draws. 
“There’s a change in our playing style, but we’ve improved with each game. I’m sure we will get the results soon,” said Azamuddin. 
“Tomorrow is a must-win game for us. And I’m confident of getting the result if we stick to our game plan.
